page.title: 10NEWTS AND FROGS
page.content: Newts are creatures that like the running water of Dorsets streams and rivers.They are sometimes are found in horse troughs where they can go deep out of the sun.In Dorset we have two of the three English species these are;the common newt or smooth newt and palmate newt. Frogs come from frogspawn which is found in murky pools.Frogs also have homes built in marsh land and pools and same as the newt they have a couple of species in the area the common frog is the most prolific frog in the area.They like small pools and like newts are sometimes found in horse troughs.The others are only a little different and are the common european frog which likes the same habitat.
